Title: Attractive Forces Between Electrons in QED$_{3}$
Authors: H. O. Girotti , M. Gomes, J. L. deLyra, R. S. Mendes, J. R. S.
  Nascimento and A. J. da Silva
Comments: revtex, 10 pages and four figures, IFUSP/P-986
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 69 (1992) 2623-2626
\\
  Vacuum polarization effects are non-perturbatively incorporated into the
photon propagator to eliminate the severe infrared problems characteristic of
QED$_3$. The theory is thus rephrased in terms of a massive vector boson whose
mass is $e^2/(8\pi)$. Subsequently, it is shown that electron-electron bound
states are possible in QED$_3$.
